            <h3>DEPARTMENT OF ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING</h3>
            <p>
                The Department of Electronics Engineering at <strong>Government Polytechnic Siwan</strong> is a progressive and innovation-driven academic department committed to developing skilled, competent, and industry-ready diploma engineers for the rapidly evolving electronics and allied sectors. The department offers a <strong>Diploma in Electronics Engineering,</strong> designed to provide students with a strong theoretical foundation complemented by extensive hands-on practical training.
            </p>
            <p>
                Electronics Engineering plays a pivotal role in modern technologies such as communication systems, automation, consumer electronics, embedded systems, industrial electronics, and emerging digital applications. Keeping pace with these advancements, the department follows an outcome-based and industry-oriented curriculum that integrates core concepts with practical applications. The programme covers key areas including electronic devices and circuits, analog and digital electronics, microprocessors and microcontrollers, embedded systems, industrial electronics, communication systems, instrumentation, and basic automation technologies.
            </p>
            <p>
                The department is supported by a team of well-qualified, experienced, and dedicated faculty members who adopt student-centric and innovative teaching–learning methodologies. Classroom instruction is reinforced through laboratory experiments, mini-projects, seminars, workshops, industrial visits, and expert lectures. Faculty members actively mentor students, encouraging analytical thinking, innovation, and problem-solving abilities while instilling professional ethics and discipline.
            </p>
            <p>
                Well-equipped laboratories form the backbone of practical training, providing students with hands-on experience in electronic circuit design, testing, troubleshooting, and system integration. Students are trained to use modern instruments, simulation tools, and electronic hardware, enabling them to confidently apply theoretical knowledge to real-world technological challenges.
            </p>
            <p>
                The Department of Electronics Engineering maintains strong linkages with industry and works closely with the institute’s Training & Placement Cell to facilitate industrial training, internships, and placement opportunities. Graduates of the programme find employment in electronics manufacturing units, communication and networking companies, automation and instrumentation industries, consumer electronics firms, and public sector undertakings. The programme also serves as a solid foundation for students aspiring to pursue higher education through lateral entry into engineering degree programmes.
            </p>
            <p>
                Beyond academics, the department actively encourages student participation in co-curricular and extracurricular activities, innovation and skill development programmes, technical competitions, and community outreach initiatives. These engagements foster creativity, teamwork, leadership, and adaptability—qualities essential for success in today’s technology-driven world.
            </p>
            <p>
                With a strong commitment to academic excellence, practical competence, innovation, and societal relevance, the Department of Electronics Engineering at Government Polytechnic Siwan strives to nurture future-ready electronics professionals capable of contributing meaningfully to technological advancement and national development.
            </p>
            <h4>Vision of the Diploma in Electronics Engineering Programme</h4>
            <p>
                To develop competent, innovative, and ethically responsible electronics engineering diploma graduates who apply foundational engineering knowledge, modern electronic technologies, and sustainable practices to meet industry needs and contribute to societal advancement.
            </p>
            <h4>Mission of the Diploma in Electronics Engineering Programme</h4>
            <p>
                <strong>M1. </strong>
                To impart strong theoretical foundations and practical skills in electronics engineering through outcome-based education that fosters critical thinking, creativity, and professional ethics.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>M2. </strong>
                To provide experiential learning through well-equipped laboratories, projects, industrial exposure, and the use of modern electronic tools to prepare students for employment, entrepreneurship, and higher education in a rapidly evolving technological environment.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>M3. </strong>
                To inculcate awareness of safety, sustainability, teamwork, and lifelong learning to enable graduates to responsibly apply electronics engineering solutions for societal benefit.
            </p>
            <h4>Programme Educational Objectives (PEOs)</h4>
            <p>
                Within three to five years of graduation, the Diploma in Electronics Engineering graduates will be able to:
            </p>
            <strong>PEO 1: Technical Competence and Problem Solving</strong>
            <p> 
                Apply principles of mathematics, science, and electronics engineering to analyze and solve well-defined problems related to electronic circuits, systems, and applications using standard engineering methods.
            </p>
            <strong>PEO 2: Professional Practice and Career Development</strong>
            <p>
                Demonstrate professional growth by effectively using modern electronic tools, testing techniques, and project management skills while adapting to technological advancements in industry, public sector, or higher education pathways.
            </p>
            <strong>PEO 3: Ethical Practice and Societal Responsibility</strong>
            <p>
                Practice electronics engineering solutions with due consideration to safety, sustainability, environmental protection, and ethical values, contributing responsibly to societal and technological development.
            </p>
            <h4>Programme Specific Outcomes (PSOs)</h4>
            <strong>PSO 1: Electronics Systems and Circuit Applications</strong>
            <p>
                Apply electronics engineering principles to design assistance, testing, troubleshooting, and maintenance of analog, digital, communication, and embedded electronic systems using appropriate tools and techniques.
            </p>
            <strong>PSO 2: Industry Readiness and Practical Implementation</strong>
            <p>
                Demonstrate hands-on competence in operating electronic instruments, performing measurements, supporting automation and communication systems, and adhering to safety, sustainability, and professional standards in real-world industrial environments.
            </p>
          
